        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-25T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-25T09:00:00-05:00" n="503" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Council/9–2545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>, Temporarily
                        in the United Kingdom, to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-25T15:00:00+01:00">September 25, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 25—12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9915. Delsec 56, September 25. Please let me know urgently whether in accepting
                    our proposal for establishment of Far Eastern Advisory Commission China and the
                    Soviet Union have accepted our proposal that other nations named in our
                    transmitting message would be invited to take part in the commission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
